ZCZC GE17
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
WEDNESDAY TO SATURDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND
COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 142300 UTC
LOW PRESSURE WILL COVER MOST OF THE BRITISH ISLES AND
SURROUNDING WATERS ON WEDNESDAY EVENING WITH THE MAIN
CENTRE OF THE LOW 981 OVER CENTRAL PARTS OF ENGLAND.
DURING THURSDAY THE LOW CENTRE IS EXP TO MOV NE INTO THE
NERN N SEA 981 AND THEN AWAY NE INTO SCANDINAVIA DURING
FRIDAY. LATER ON FRIDAY AND DURING SATURDAY A RIDGE OF
HIGH PRESSURE IS EXP TO BUILD FM THE W ACROSS THE BRITISH
ISLES. STRG WINDS ARE EXP TO AFFECT MOST AREAS ON
WEDNESDAY EVENING AND DURING THURSDAY AND FRIDAY WITH A
RISK OF GALES FOR A TIME ACROSS NERN PARTS OF THE N SEA
ON WEDNESDAY EVENING AND AT FIRST ON THURSDAY AND ALSO
ACROSS MOST OF THE N SEA FOR A TIME LATER ON THURSDAY AND
AT FIRST ON FRIDAY. WINDS ARE EXP TO EASE ACROSS ALL
AREAS LATER ON FRIDAY AND DURING SATURDAY
